        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="474" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/2–146: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Political Adviser in Korea</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Benninghoff</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-07">February 7,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. Moscow tel 310 Feb 1 follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Soviet press Feb 1 carries Tass Chungking despatch on differences,
                            within Kim Koo ‘govt’. Quotes Seoul correspondent of <hi rend="italic">Central News</hi> that Kim Koo has admitted split in his
                            organization and confirmed report Kim Choo Si and Kim Yak San have left
                            so-called National Liberation Committee. Gives reason for split as Kim
                            Koo’s full alignment with rightist elements.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
